d the lowest sensory responses to both hindlimbs. Conclusion: The results suggest that rTMS therapy beginning in the acute phase after SCI promotes neuroplasticity and is an effective rehabilitative approach in a rat model of SCI.},
author = {Krishnan, Vijai S. and Shin, Samuel S. and Belegu, Visar and Celnik, Pablo and Reimers, Mark and Smith, Kylie R. and Pelled, Galit},
doi = {10.3389/fnins.2019.00387},
file = {:Users/juandp77/Dropbox/references/Frontiers in Neuroscience/Multimodal evaluation of TMS - Induced somatosensory plasticity and behavioral recovery in rats with contusion spinal cord injury - Kris.pdf:pdf},
